  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n---\n## 2026-03-30 19:25 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 4] F&G Correlation + Monday Trade Review\n\n**Task:** Correlate Fear & Greed with WR. Review first Monday with new filters.\n\n**Findings:**\n1. **F&G is useless as a signal right now** \u2014 ALL 161 trades happened during Extreme Fear (F&G 0-19). No data for other regimes. Can't correlate what doesn't vary.\n2. **Monday results: 3W/2L = 60% WR on 5 trades** (outcomes say 5, but logs show 6 executions). All YES bets at hour 11-12.\n3. **Duplicate trade bug is BACK** \u2014 two trades 7 seconds apart at 11:19 (same 5-min window), two more at 11:38-11:39. Per-window guard is broken.\n4. **Hour 19 completely blocked** \u2014 UP price at $0.540 > max_price $0.535. 46 price blocks today. Our second-best hour is being wasted.\n5. **V3.2 filter blocks NO trades at hour 11** \u2014 \"YES-only, NO=40% WR\". Forces us to wait for negative bias to buy YES.\n\n**My thinking:** Two competing problems:\n- max_price at $0.535 is too tight, blocking our best hours \u2192 should widen to $0.545\n- BUT higher price = higher break-even WR needed (54.5% at $0.545)\n- The duplicate trade bug is more urgent \u2014 it doubles our risk per window\n\n**Decision:** Fix duplicate bug first (P2 priority). Widen max_price to $0.545 with data backing needed. F&G not actionable until we trade in non-fear regime.\n\n**Next P4:** Build BTC volatility regime classifier (ATR-based). More useful differentiator than F&G.\n\n## 2026-03-31 03:08 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 4] Fixed Copy Scanner Cron Logging\n\n**Task:** Fix copy_scanner_v2 cron not writing to log file.\n\n**Root cause:** Crontab defaulted to `/bin/sh` which doesn't support `source` command. The cron entry uses `source venv/bin/activate` \u2014 this silently fails in sh, so python3 runs without venv, likely fails on import, and produces no output.\n\n**Fix:** Added `SHELL=/bin/bash` to crontab header. Verified: log grew from 13\u219226 lines after next cron tick. \u2705\n\n**Impact:** Copy scanner signal file was only updating sporadically (when manually run). Now it updates every 5 min as designed. This means the bot's copy signal was often stale \u2014 the 213-min gap identified earlier was caused by this bug. With the fix, copy_signal.json will always be fresh.\n\n**Current signal:** neutral@2% (3 AM, low liquidity, balanced OB).\n\n## 2026-03-31 02:42 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 3] W14 Day 1 Summary + Shadow Update\n\n**Task:** Write W14 Day 1 weekly review summary. Check shadow outcomes.\n\n**Shadow Trades Update:** 3 outcomes now: 2W/1L (67% WR)\n- 01:10 h=1: \u2705 BTC +$154\n- 02:05 h=2: \u2705 BTC +$2 (barely)\n- 02:35 h=2: \u274c BTC -$28\n\n67% in excluded hours during a rally \u2014 interesting but n=3. Momentum periods can briefly make any hour profitable. The real test is sustained WR over weeks.\n\n**W14 Day 1 Summary written:** `reports/weekly-review-2026-W14-day1.md`\nComplete Day 1 audit: 71% WR, 4 bugs fixed, regime filter validated, infrastructure deployed.\n\n**PM Balance:** Still $921.75 after 6.5h. May need manual ",
